[SN]TITLE[SN]
Knife attacker chased off by Flixton shopkeeper

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A "brave" shopkeeper chased a knife-wielding robber out of a Greater Manchester convenience store despite being attacked and stabbed.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
24 April 2015 Last updated at 13:22 BST
The offender is pictured on CCTV entering Premier Stores on Carrington Road, Flixton, on 14 April threatening the and demanding cash.
After toppling over the counter, a fight ensues between the thief and the shopkeeper.
Police said the "brave" worker suffered cuts to his ear and finger during the incident.
